[h1]Skill Books — Writing[/h1]

[b]Skill books no longer drop as loot. Your survivors [i]write[/i] them — from what they actually know.[/b]

Knowledge stops being a lucky find on a shelf and becomes something the experienced members of your community produce and pass down. Built for big dedicated / multiplayer servers: all the heavy lifting happens once at world boot, so there is [b]zero[/b] runtime loot overhead.

[hr][/hr]
[h2]What it does[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]No more skill-book loot[/b] — vanilla skill books stop spawning everywhere (houses, libraries, stores, vehicles, trash…).
[*][b]Write skill books[/b] — produce a book for a skill you're good at, for others to read.
[*][b]Books for skills that never had one[/b] — Strength, Fitness and the melee skills, enabled per category by the admin.
[/list]
It [b]does not[/b] change how reading a book grants XP — it uses the vanilla system untouched. It only removes the loot and adds a way to make books.

[hr][/hr]
[h2]How writing works[/h2]
[olist]
[*][b]Bind an Empty Skill Book[/b] — a simple craft any survivor can do from the start, on any surface. Uses a notebook/journal/diary + glue + leather strips + thread.
[*][b]Write it[/b] — right-click the Empty Skill Book → [i]Write skill book[/i] → choose a skill → choose a volume. You need a [b]pen or pencil[/b] on you.
[/olist]
A skill/volume only shows up when you're skilled enough: [b]level ≥ 2 × tier[/b] (Vol. 1 needs level 2, Vol. 5 needs level 10). Writing higher volumes takes longer (configurable).

[i]You write books mostly for lower-level players to read — by the time you can write Volume 1, you've already outgrown it. It's a knowledge economy, not a personal shortcut.[/i]

[hr][/hr]
[h2]Multiplayer-ready[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Server-authoritative[/b] — the server validates your skill level, the writing tool and the blank book before creating anything. No client-side forging.
[*][b]Instant sync[/b] — the written book appears immediately, no relog.
[*][b]Performance[/b] — one item scan + one loot-table pass at boot; nothing per tick, nothing on loot rolls.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]
[h2]Works with other mods[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Writable automatically[/b] — books from mods that follow the vanilla convention (e.g. [b]Lifestyle[/b]: Cleaning / Music / Dancing, and others) can be written without any hard dependency. Toggle with [i]Allow writing modded books[/i].
[*][b]Loot removal also covers modded books — with one limit.[/b] Modded skill books that register into the loot tables the normal (vanilla) way [b]can[/b] be stopped from spawning, together with the vanilla ones (scope [i]All[/i]). But mods that inject and re-bake their own loot a [i]different[/i] way after the distribution merge — like [b]Lifestyle[/b] — are [b]not[/b] affected: their books keep spawning. Use scope [i]Vanilla only[/i] to strip the base-game books exclusively.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]
[h2]Sandbox options[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Disable skill book spawns[/b] — turn the loot removal on/off, with an All / Vanilla-only scope.
[*][b]Allow writing vanilla books[/b] and [b]modded books[/b] — toggle each source.
[*][b]Passive-skill books[/b] (Strength, Fitness, Sprinting, Lightfooted, Nimble, Sneaking) — off by default.
[*][b]Combat-skill books[/b] (Axe, Long Blunt, Short Blunt, Short Blade, Spear) — off by default.
[*][b]Writing time[/b] — base time + per-tier multiplier.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]
[h2]Languages[/h2]
English and Português (Brasil).

[b]Want the mod in your language?[/b] It's only a few dozen short lines and anyone can help — no coding needed. See [url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/discussion/3743350882/561409854000903256/]How to help translate the mod[/url].

[hr][/hr]
[i]Build 42. Safe to add mid-save: already-spawned books are not touched; only future loot stops carrying them.[/i]

